This directory's actual YoutubeVault.apk is placed here by CI (see the
publish-frontend job in .github/workflows/docker-publish.yml, which downloads
the android-apk job's freshly built artifact into this exact path before the
Docker image builds) — never committed, so this placeholder is what keeps the
directory itself present in git.

A local `docker compose up --build` without going through CI won't have an
apk here, so /download/YoutubeVault.apk will 404 — harmless for local dev,
where the frontend is normally run via `npm run dev` anyway (see README).
